SIMPLE: embassador
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embassador
<hw>Em*bas"sa*dor</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr></mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Embassador</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A minister of the highest
rank sent to a foreign court to represent there his sovereign or
country.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <ex>Ambassadors</ex> are either <xex>ordinary</xex> [or
<xex>resident</xex>] or <xex>extraordinary</xex>, that is, sent upon
some special or unusual occasion or errand.</note>
<rj><au>Abbott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An official messenger and representative.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambassadorial</ent>⟦br⟧
